result.execSummary:
The defendant Rolland James Starr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Rolland James Starr in court with attorney Jeffery Joy.  Defendant Rolland James Starr in custody.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:59 PM. Called 15CF77 & 15CF111. State - resolved - 15CF77 - #1 - DRI, #2 - moves to amend to possession of THC 1st offense with PTAC, fine of $1000.00 plus costs, 45 days in FC jail; 15CF111 - amend count #1 to 946.41(1) - obstructing an officer (reads new penalties), joint recommendation of costs, 30 days in FC jail - consecutive to 15CF77, count #2 - moves to amend to county ordinance of DC with forfeiture of $1,000.00 plus costs. Joy and Starr agree. Court - 15CF77 - court DRI count #1, amends count #2 to possession of THC as PTAC as 1st offense and deleting 2nd or subsequent offense - reads new charge and penalty. Starr pleads G to count #2 as amended. Court - 15CF11 - court amends count #1 to obstructing an officer contrary to 961.41(1) - reads new charge and penalty. Starr pleads G to count #1 as amended. Court amends count #2 to county ordinance of bail jumping - pleads G, finds G, forfeiture of $1,000.00 plus costs- take bond posted - 60 DTP/CO. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights and right to JT by entering his plea, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Joy makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation - asking for short furlough from tomorrow (2/11/16) to Sunday (2/14/16) at 5:00 PM for stated reasons - 20 days credit on 15CF77 and 5 days credit on 15CF111 (State stipulates). Starr makes statement, remorseful. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 15CF77 - count #2 - fine of $1000.00 plus costs and surcharges - take bond posted - remainder due in 60 days/CO, 45 days in FC jail - huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(3) - credit for 20 days - stayed until no later than 2/15/16 at 8:30 AM; 15CF111 - count #1 - costs - 60 DTP/CO, 30 days in FC jail - consecutive to jail time on 15CF77 - huber and good time allowed - credit for 5 days - eligible for community service under 973.03(3) - stayed until no later than 8:30 AM on 2/15/16, in regards to request for furlough (State does not object to the furlough request), modifies bond on both cases to $1000.00 signature bond with no consumption of alcohol, authorizes expungement under 973.015 upon completion of sentence and payment in full of fines, release from jail today until time of report on or no later than 2/15/16 at 8:30 AM, submit DNA sample with expunction rights, right to appeal, adjourned.

Defendant Rolland James Starr in court with attorney Jeffery Joy.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 3:51 PM. Also called 15CF111. Joy - not resolved and believes that the defendant will be terminating him on both cases. Starr agrees. Court makes statement that it would be unfair to all parties at this point to dismiss Mr. Joy from the case at this late stage. Joy has gone over the defendant's chance of success at trial, offer was - reduction in charges on 15CF111 and plead to misd theft and jail for 30 days after amended to obsturcting justice, amending felony BJ to county ordinance of BJ. Starr agrees. State makes comment in regards to one of the witnesses that have been subpoenaed for tomorrow's JT, offer on 15CF77 - count #1 - DRI, #2 - amend to 1st offense possession of THC with PTAC,  45 days jail and $1000.00 fine plus costs. Joy and Starr agree. State - will need to take 15CF111 case as #1 tomorrow for stated reasons. Joy makes statement, respectfully asks that the trial be adjourned for stated reasons. State asks for clarification of Joy's statement. Court increases bond to $5000.00 cash on each case to make sure the defendant will be here for tomorrow's JT, Court will be calling in the jury, condition of bond on this matter that he is to have no contact with Yance Mann and no one else is to have contact with Yance Mann. Joy makes statement. Record reflects that the defendant's demeanor today is disrespectful to the Court. Court sets 15CF111 for 1 day JT on 2/12/16, State will get witnesses for both cases subpoenaed.  Jury trial scheduled for February 12, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Rolland James Starr in court with attorney Jeffery Joy.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 4:35 PM. Also called 15CF111. State - not resolved. Joy and Starr agree. Starr understands the ramifications of rejecting the plea. Court continues bond on both cases, sets both matters for JT.  Jury trial scheduled for January 28, 2016 at 08:30 am.
